Distribution (
Fig. 19
). NORTH AMERICA , CANADA , and USA . Transcontinental from eastern

British Columbia to Nova Scotia , south to Central Colorado Rocky Mountains in the western populations. A record from western Arizona and one from north central New Mexico (
Snow 1881
) may be accidental. The eastern population occurs from Canada to the extreme north of Georgia and South Carolina in the Appalachian Mountains. The map point on Mobile, Alabama does not represent a naturalized population (
Atkinson et al. 1991
).
